      <li><p>Rooms are valid for 12 hours only.</p></li>
      <li><p>Supported browsers: Google chrome, Firefox and Safari</p></li>
      <li><p>Internet explorer is not supported</p></li>
      <li><p>Built with Webrtc, video and chat is encrypted and peer to peer, that means its secure and private. It does not go through any server.</p></li>
      <li><p>Screensharing is only available when connected to a peer or peers.</p></li>
      <li><p>Chat is only available when connected to a peer or peers.</p></li>
    </ul>
    <ul class="tab_content" 
      x-cloak
      x-show="info_how_to_modal_state.how_to">
      <li>
        <p class="title">CREATE A MEETING ROOM</p>
        <p>Click on the blue button in landing and you will be redirected to the room you just created.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="title">INVITE A PEER</p>
        <p>Before entering the meeting room, there is an input field where you can put your peers email address and send the link of the room for them to join. </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="title">SETUP PARTICIPANT NAME, CAMERA AND MICROPHONE</p>
        <p>Before entering the meeting room, click on gear icon. The devices settings screen will appear and you can choose your devices and enter your participant name.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="title">IN CALL SETTINGS: TOGGLE CAMERA AND MICROPHONE</p>
        <p>In call, open the in-call settings found in the left side of the screen. Click on the camera icon to toggle on-off your camera and click on the microphone icon to toggle on-off your microphone.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="title">IN CALL SETTINGS: SCREENSHARE</p>
        <p>In call, open the in-call settings found in the left side of the screen. Click on the screen share icon to open screenshare and select the screen you want to share. To turn off, click on stop sharing button found on the bottom part of the screen.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="title">IN CALL: CHAT</p>
        <p>In call, click on the chat button on the right side of the screen to toggle the chat window. Select your peer in the chat channel selection and send your message.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="title">IN CALL: SENDING FILES</p>
        <p>In call, click on the chat button on the right side of the screen to toggle the chat window. You can drag the files you want to send onto the textarea or click on the file icon on the text area to open and select the files you want to send.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
